{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FKfPHC4wrtF3gJv1rFh9Pb","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# BLIS Policy Config: llm-d EPP Precise Prefix Cache\n     2→#\n     3→# Maps llm-d's epp-precise-prefix-cache-config.yaml to BLIS policy config.\n     4→# This is the recommended production configuration for cache-aware routing.\n     5→#\n     6→# ============================================================================\n     7→# llm-d Source: deploy/config/epp-precise-prefix-cache-config.yaml\n     8→# ============================================================================\n     9→#\n    10→#   schedulingProfiles:\n    11→#     - name: default\n    12→#       plugins:\n    13→#         - pluginRef: precise-prefix-cache-scorer\n    14→#           weight: 2.0\n    15→#         - pluginRef: kv-cache-utilization-scorer\n    16→#           weight: 1.0\n    17→#         - pluginRef: queue-scorer\n    18→#           weight: 1.0\n    19→#\n    20→# ============================================================================\n    21→# Scorer Mapping:\n    22→# ============================================================================\n    23→#\n    24→#   | llm-d Scorer                  | BLIS Scorer      | Formula                              |\n    25→#   |-------------------------------|------------------|--------------------------------------|\n    26→#   | precise-prefix-cache-scorer   | prefix-affinity  | matchedBlocks / totalBlocks          |\n    27→#   | kv-cache-utilization-scorer   | kv-utilization   | 1 - KVCacheUsagePercent              |\n    28→#   | queue-scorer                  | queue-depth      | (max - val) / (max - min)            |\n    29→#\n    30→# Note: llm-d's precise-prefix-cache-scorer tracks real-time KV cache state via\n    31→# kvevents from vLLM instances. BLIS's prefix-affinity uses router-side estimation\n    32→# based on routing history. Both compute: matchedBlocks / totalBlocks.\n    33→#\n    34→# ============================================================================\n    35→# Weight Ratios:\n    36→# ============================================================================\n    37→#\n    38→#   llm-d:  prefix:2.0, kv-util:1.0, queue:1.0  (sum=4.0)\n    39→#   BLIS:   prefix:2.0, kv-util:1.0, queue:1.0  (normalized internally)\n    40→#\n    41→# The 2:1:1 ratio prioritizes prefix cache locality over load distribution,\n    42→# matching llm-d's production recommendation.\n    43→#\n    44→# ============================================================================\n    45→# Usage:\n    46→# ============================================================================\n    47→#\n    48→#   ./simulation_worker run \\\n    49→#     --model meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct \\\n    50→#     --num-instances 4 \\\n    51→#     --policy-config examples/epp-precise-prefix.yaml \\\n    52→#     --workload-spec examples/prefix-affinity-demo.yaml \\\n    53→#     --trace-level decisions --summarize-trace\n    54→#\n    55→# Or via CLI:\n    56→#\n    57→#   --routing-policy weighted \\\n    58→#   --routing-scorers \"prefix-affinity:2,kv-utilization:1,queue-depth:1\"\n    59→#\n    60→\n    61→admission:\n    62→  policy: always-admit\n    63→\n    64→routing:\n    65→  policy: weighted\n    66→  scorers:\n    67→    # precise-prefix-cache-scorer → prefix-affinity\n    68→    # Score = matchedBlocks / totalBlocks\n    69→    - name: prefix-affinity\n    70→      weight: 2.0\n    71→\n    72→    # kv-cache-utilization-scorer → kv-utilization\n    73→    # Score = 1 - KVUtilization\n    74→    # Note: KV utilization is a lagging signal at high rates (R17). The queue-depth\n    75→    # scorer compensates — do not remove it from this configuration.\n    76→    - name: kv-utilization\n    77→      weight: 1.0\n    78→\n    79→    # queue-scorer → queue-depth\n    80→    # Score = (maxQueue - queue) / (maxQueue - minQueue)\n    81→    - name: queue-depth\n    82→      weight: 1.0\n    83→\n    84→priority:\n    85→  policy: constant\n    86→\n    87→scheduler: fcfs\n    88→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012b8C2oTh4sYG3eyvLd5GtZ","session_id":"9f2cfc56-8ee0-4275-935a-cec6cd97b7f9","uuid":"d1f6517d-9aac-45b3-b8bd-ed86d8bb637f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TA3TtgyxZEG5Kh2G7fxKMZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# BLIS Policy Config: llm-d EPP Estimate Prefix Cache\n     2→#\n     3→# Maps llm-d's epp-estimate-prefix-cache-config.yaml to BLIS policy config.\n     4→# This configuration uses router-side prefix estimation (not real-time KV cache tracking).\n     5→#\n     6→# ============================================================================\n     7→# llm-d Source: deploy/config/epp-estimate-prefix-cache-config.yaml\n     8→# ============================================================================\n     9→#\n    10→#   schedulingProfiles:\n    11→#     - name: default\n    12→#       plugins:\n    13→#         - pluginRef: prefix-cache-scorer\n    14→#           weight: 1.0\n    15→#         - pluginRef: load-aware-scorer\n    16→#           weight: 1.0\n    17→#\n    18→# ============================================================================\n    19→# Scorer Mapping:\n    20→# ============================================================================\n    21→#\n    22→#   | llm-d Scorer          | BLIS Scorer      | Notes                                |\n    23→#   |-----------------------|------------------|--------------------------------------|\n    24→#   | prefix-cache-scorer   | prefix-affinity  | Router-side prefix estimation        |\n    25→#   | load-aware-scorer     | load-balance     | See formula differences below        |\n    26→#\n    27→# Formula Differences:\n    28→#   - llm-d load-aware-scorer: 0.5 * (1 - waitingRequests/threshold), range [0, 0.5]\n    29→#   - BLIS load-balance:       1 / (1 + effectiveLoad), range (0, 1]\n    30→#\n    31→# Both formulas give higher scores to less-loaded instances, but with different\n    32→# scaling. For simulation purposes, the relative ordering is preserved.\n    33→#\n    34→# ============================================================================\n    35→# Usage:\n    36→# ============================================================================\n    37→#\n    38→#   ./simulation_worker run \\\n    39→#     --model meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct \\\n    40→#     --num-instances 4 \\\n    41→#     --policy-config examples/epp-estimate-prefix.yaml \\\n    42→#     --workload-spec examples/prefix-affinity-demo.yaml \\\n    43→#     --trace-level decisions --summarize-trace\n    44→#\n    45→\n    46→admission:\n    47→  policy: always-admit\n    48→\n    49→routing:\n    50→  policy: weighted\n    51→  scorers:\n    52→    # prefix-cache-scorer → prefix-affinity\n    53→    # Both use router-side estimation of prefix cache state\n    54→    - name: prefix-affinity\n    55→      weight: 1.0\n    56→\n    57→    # load-aware-scorer → load-balance\n    58→    # llm-d: 0.5 * (1 - waiting/threshold)\n    59→    # BLIS: 1 / (1 + effectiveLoad)\n    60→    - name: load-balance\n    61→      weight: 1.0\n    62→\n    63→priority:\n    64→  policy: constant\n    65→\n    66→scheduler: fcfs\n    67→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012b8C2oTh4sYG3eyvLd5GtZ","session_id":"9f2cfc56-8ee0-4275-935a-cec6cd97b7f9","uuid":"e76a127b-276c-4901-a658-7f010a863268"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016HbHhFJf2FduaXJE3NwvUC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# BLIS Weighted Routing — Composable Scorer Pipeline\n     2→#\n     3→# The `weighted` routing policy aggregates multiple scoring dimensions,\n     4→# each evaluating instances on a [0,1] scale. Scores are combined with\n     5→# configurable weights: score = clamp(s_i) * w_i, then argmax.\n     6→#\n     7→# Available scorers:\n     8→#   prefix-affinity — proportional prefix match ratio via router-side cache\n     9→#   queue-depth     — min-max normalization of effective load (llm-d match)\n    10→#   kv-utilization  — inverse utilization: 1 - KVUtilization (llm-d match)\n    11→#   load-balance    — inverse transform: 1/(1 + effectiveLoad) (BLIS-native)\n    12→#\n    13→# Default profile (when --routing-scorers is not specified):\n    14→#   prefix-affinity:3, queue-depth:2, kv-utilization:2 (llm-d parity)\n    15→#\n    16→# Weights are relative — only ratios matter. [3,2,2] behaves identically\n    17→# to [0.43,0.29,0.29]. The framework normalizes weights to sum to 1.0.\n    18→#\n    19→# ============================================================================\n    20→# TRY IT: Compare scorer configurations\n    21→# ============================================================================\n    22→#\n    23→#   # Default profile (llm-d parity: prefix-affinity dominant)\n    24→#   ./simulation_worker run \\\n    25→#     --model meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct \\\n    26→#     --num-instances 4 --routing-policy weighted \\\n    27→#     --workload-spec examples/servegen-language.yaml \\\n    28→#     --trace-level decisions --summarize-trace\n    29→#\n    30→#   # Prefix-affinity dominant (maximize cache reuse)\n    31→#   ./simulation_worker run \\\n    32→#     --model meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct \\\n    33→#     --num-instances 4 --routing-policy weighted \\\n    34→#     --routing-scorers \"prefix-affinity:5,queue-depth:1\" \\\n    35→#     --workload-spec examples/servegen-language.yaml \\\n    36→#     --trace-level decisions --summarize-trace\n    37→#\n    38→#   # Load-balance only (no prefix awareness, equivalent to least-loaded)\n    39→#   ./simulation_worker run \\\n    40→#     --model meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct \\\n    41→#     --num-instances 4 --routing-policy weighted \\\n    42→#     --routing-scorers \"load-balance:1\" \\\n    43→#     --workload-spec examples/servegen-language.yaml \\\n    44→#     --trace-level decisions --summarize-trace\n    45→#\n    46→# ============================================================================\n    47→# Adding new scorers\n    48→# ============================================================================\n    49→#\n    50→# To add a new scorer:\n    51→# 1. Implement the scorer function in sim/routing_scorers.go (or a new file\n    52→#    like sim/routing_prefix_scorer.go for stateful scorers)\n    53→# 2. Register the name in validScorerNames + newScorerWithObserver factory\n    54→# Extension friction: 2 touch points.\n    55→\n    56→admission:\n    57→  policy: always-admit\n    58→\n    59→routing:\n    60→  policy: weighted\n    61→  scorers:\n    62→    - name: prefix-affinity\n    63→      weight: 3.0\n    64→    - name: queue-depth\n    65→      weight: 2.0\n    66→    - name: kv-utilization\n    67→      weight: 2.0\n    68→\n    69→priority:\n    70→  policy: constant\n    71→\n    72→scheduler: fcfs\n    73→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012b8C2oTh4sYG3eyvLd5GtZ","session_id":"9f2cfc56-8ee0-4275-935a-cec6cd97b7f9","uuid":"d159aa4d-e641-4a30-926c-6547c7c8e45c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012b8C2oTh4sYG3eyvLd5GtZ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a comprehensive picture. Here is a detailed report of my findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. WorkloadSpec v2 Validation -- Required Fields and Rules\n\n**File:** `/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/stepml-worktrees/round4-idea-2-cycle-time-regression/sim/workload/spec.go`\n\n### Top-Level `WorkloadSpec` Struct (lines 41-51)\n\n```go\ntype WorkloadSpec struct {\n    Version       string            `yaml:\"version\"`\n    Seed          int64             `yaml:\"seed\"`\n    Category      string            `yaml:\"category\"`\n    Clients       []ClientSpec      `yaml:\"clients\"`\n    AggregateRate float64           `yaml:\"aggregate_rate\"`\n    Horizon       int64             `yaml:\"horizon,omitempty\"`\n    NumRequests   int64             `yaml:\"num_requests,omitempty\"`\n    ServeGenData  *ServeGenDataSpec `yaml:\"servegen_data,omitempty\"`\n    InferencePerf *InferencePerfSpec `yaml:\"inference_perf,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Validation Rules (from `Validate()` at lines 167-183)\n\nThe `Validate()` method enforces these constraints at the top level:\n\n1. **`category`** -- Must be one of: `\"\"` (empty), `\"language\"`, `\"multimodal\"`, `\"reasoning\"`. Anything else produces an error.\n\n2. **`aggregate_rate`** -- Must be **strictly positive** (> 0). This is always required.\n\n3. **`clients`** -- At least one client is required, **unless** `servegen_data` is provided. The check is: `len(s.Clients) == 0 && s.ServeGenData == nil` produces an error.\n\n4. Each client in the `clients` array is validated individually via `validateClient()`.\n\n### Per-Client Validation (`validateClient()` at lines 185-217)\n\nEach `ClientSpec` is validated with these rules:\n\n| Field | Requirement |\n|---|---|\n| `slo_class` | Must be one of: `\"\"`, `\"critical\"`, `\"standard\"`, `\"sheddable\"`, `\"batch\"`, `\"background\"` |\n| `rate_fraction` | Must be **strictly positive** (> 0) |\n| `arrival.process` | Must be one of: `\"poisson\"`, `\"gamma\"`, `\"weibull\"`, `\"constant\"` |\n| `arrival.cv` (optional) | If provided, must be finite and positive. If process is `\"weibull\"`, additionally constrained to `[0.01, 10.4]` |\n| `prefix_length` | Must be non-negative (>= 0) |\n| `input_distribution` | Validated via `validateDistSpec()` |\n| `output_distribution` | Validated via `validateDistSpec()` |\n\n### Distribution Validation (`validateDistSpec()` at lines 219-229)\n\nEach `DistSpec` is validated:\n\n| Field | Requirement |\n|---|---|\n| `type` | Must be one of: `\"gaussian\"`, `\"exponential\"`, `\"pareto_lognormal\"`, `\"empirical\"`, `\"constant\"` |\n| `params` (map values) | Every value must be finite -- no `NaN` or `Inf` allowed |\n\n### Loading and Strict Parsing (`LoadWorkloadSpec()` at lines 151-164)\n\nWhen loading from YAML:\n- **Strict YAML parsing** is enabled via `decoder.KnownFields(true)` (Rule R10) -- any unrecognized/typo'd YAML key is rejected as an error.\n- After parsing, `UpgradeV1ToV2()` is automatically called, which maps deprecated v1 SLO class names (`\"realtime\"` -> `\"critical\"`, `\"interactive\"` -> `\"standard\"`) and sets `Version` to `\"2\"`.\n\n### Fields That Are NOT Explicitly Validated\n\nThese fields exist in the struct but are not checked by `Validate()`:\n- `version` -- Set automatically by `UpgradeV1ToV2()` but not range-checked.\n- `seed` -- No validation (any int64 is accepted).\n- `horizon` -- No validation (optional, omitempty).\n- `num_requests` -- No validation (0 = unlimited).\n- Client-level: `id`, `tenant_id`, `model`, `prefix_group`, `streaming`, `network`, `lifecycle`, `multimodal`, `reasoning` -- These are present in the struct but not validated by `Validate()`.\n\n### Valid Value Registries (lines 134-147)\n\nThe valid values are stored in unexported maps (per Rule R8), with a public accessor `IsValidSLOClass()`:\n\n```go\nvalidArrivalProcesses: \"poisson\", \"gamma\", \"weibull\", \"constant\"\nvalidDistTypes:        \"gaussian\", \"exponential\", \"pareto_lognormal\", \"empirical\", \"constant\"\nvalidCategories:       \"\", \"language\", \"multimodal\", \"reasoning\"\nvalidSLOClasses:       \"\", \"critical\", \"standard\", \"sheddable\", \"batch\", \"background\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. InferencePerf Section Handling\n\n**File:** `/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/stepml-worktrees/round4-idea-2-cycle-time-regression/sim/workload/inference_perf.go`\n\n### What It Is\n\nThe `inference_perf` block is an alternative, compact format for specifying workloads. Instead of manually defining many clients, you provide stage-based load patterns and shared prefix parameters, and BLIS expands them into a full `WorkloadSpec` with auto-generated clients.\n\n### InferencePerfSpec Struct (lines 14-17)\n\n```go\ntype InferencePerfSpec struct {\n    Stages       []StageSpec       `yaml:\"stages\"`\n    SharedPrefix *SharedPrefixSpec `yaml:\"shared_prefix\"`\n}\n```\n\n### StageSpec (lines 20-23)\n\n```go\ntype StageSpec struct {\n    Rate     float64 `yaml:\"rate\"`     // requests per second\n    Duration int64   `yaml:\"duration\"` // seconds\n}\n```\n\n### SharedPrefixSpec (lines 26-33)\n\n```go\ntype SharedPrefixSpec struct {\n    NumUniqueSystemPrompts  int  `yaml:\"num_unique_system_prompts\"`\n    NumUsersPerSystemPrompt int  `yaml:\"num_users_per_system_prompt\"`\n    SystemPromptLen         int  `yaml:\"system_prompt_len\"`\n    QuestionLen             int  `yaml:\"question_len\"`\n    OutputLen               int  `yaml:\"output_len\"`\n    EnableMultiTurnChat     bool `yaml:\"enable_multi_turn_chat\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Validation Rules (`validateInferencePerfSpec()` at lines 37-72)\n\n| Field | Requirement |\n|---|---|\n| `stages` | At least one stage required |\n| `stages[i].duration` | Must be positive (> 0) |\n| `stages[i].rate` | Must be finite and positive (no NaN, no Inf, > 0) |\n| `shared_prefix` | **Required** (cannot be nil) |\n| `shared_prefix.num_unique_system_prompts` | Must be positive (> 0) |\n| `shared_prefix.num_users_per_system_prompt` | Must be positive (> 0) |\n| `shared_prefix.system_prompt_len` | Must be non-negative (>= 0) |\n| `shared_prefix.question_len` | Must be non-negative (>= 0) |\n| `shared_prefix.output_len` | Must be non-negative (>= 0) |\n\n### Expansion to Full WorkloadSpec (`ExpandInferencePerfSpec()` at lines 77-157)\n\nThe expansion works as follows:\n\n1. **Validates** the spec first.\n2. Computes `numClients = NumUniqueSystemPrompts * NumUsersPerSystemPrompt`.\n3. Computes `aggregate_rate` as the **time-weighted average** across all stages: `sum(rate_i * duration_i) / sum(duration_i)`.\n4. Converts multi-stage specs into **lifecycle windows** (start/end in microseconds). Single-stage specs get no lifecycle windows (always active).\n5. Generates `N * M` clients, each with:\n   - **ID**: `prompt-{p}-user-{u}`\n   - **Tenant ID**: `prompt-{p}` (same as prefix group)\n   - **SLO class**: `\"batch\"`\n   - **Rate fraction**: `1.0 / numClients` (evenly distributed)\n   - **Arrival process**: `\"poisson\"`\n   - **Input distribution**: constant at `question_len`\n   - **Output distribution**: constant at `output_len`\n   - **Prefix group**: `prompt-{p}`\n   - **Prefix length**: `system_prompt_len`\n6. If `enable_multi_turn_chat` is true, each client also gets a `ReasoningSpec` with 5 rounds, 500ms think time, and `\"accumulate\"` context growth. The category is set to `\"reasoning\"` instead of `\"language\"`.\n\nThe output is a standard `WorkloadSpec` with `Version: \"2\"`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Example Workload Specs in the Codebase\n\nAll examples are in `/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/stepml-worktrees/round4-idea-2-cycle-time-regression/examples/`.\n\n### Workload Spec Examples (what you feed via `--workload-spec`)\n\n| File | Format | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `servegen-language.yaml` | v2 native | Two clients (batch + critical), demonstrates pareto_lognormal input dist, gamma arrivals, network specs, prefix groups. Has `num_requests: 500`. |\n| `prefix-affinity-demo.yaml` | v2 native | Two clients (80/20 split), long prefix group for prefix-affinity routing demos. |\n| `multiturn-chat-demo.yaml` | v2 native | Single client with `reasoning` spec (multi-turn, 5 rounds, context accumulation). Category: `\"reasoning\"`. |\n| `inference-perf-shared-prefix.yaml` | inference_perf format (v1) | Compact format: 2 stages (8 req/s ramp-up, 20 req/s burst), 9 prompts x 5 users = 45 auto-generated clients. |\n\n### Policy Config Examples (not workload specs, but used alongside them)\n\n| File | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `epp-estimate-prefix.yaml` | llm-d EPP estimate prefix-cache config mapped to BLIS policy |\n| `epp-precise-prefix.yaml` | llm-d EPP precise prefix-cache config (2:1:1 weights) |\n| `weighted-routing.yaml` | Composable scorer pipeline demo (3:2:2 default profile) |\n| `policy-config.yaml` | General policy config example |\n\n### Concrete Example: Minimal Valid v2 Workload Spec\n\nBased on the validation rules, a minimal valid v2 spec would need:\n\n```yaml\nversion: \"2\"\nseed: 42\naggregate_rate: 10.0      # required, must be > 0\n\nclients:                   # at least one client (unless servegen_data)\n  - rate_fraction: 1.0     # required, must be > 0\n    arrival:\n      process: poisson     # required, must be valid process\n    input_distribution:\n      type: gaussian       # required, must be valid dist type\n      params:\n        mean: 128\n        std_dev: 50\n    output_distribution:\n      type: exponential    # required, must be valid dist type\n      params:\n        mean: 64\n```\n\n### Concrete Example: Minimal Valid inference_perf Spec\n\n```yaml\nversion: \"1\"\nseed: 42\naggregate_rate: 8.0\n\ninference_perf:\n  stages:\n    - rate: 8.0\n      duration: 600\n  shared_prefix:\n    num_unique_system_prompts: 3\n    num_users_per_system_prompt: 2\n    system_prompt_len: 100\n    question_len: 200\n    output_len: 100\n    enable_multi_turn_chat: false\n```\n\nNote that the `inference_perf` spec still requires `aggregate_rate > 0` and either clients or servegen_data to pass the top-level `Validate()`. However, the `ExpandInferencePerfSpec()` function produces a complete `WorkloadSpec` with auto-generated clients, so callers typically use the expanded result rather than calling `Validate()` on the original spec containing the `inference_perf` block."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad331cf (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 3168\ntool_uses: 12\nduration_ms: 79372</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9f2cfc56-8ee0-4275-935a-cec6cd97b7f9","uuid":"e8d9b786-5d8f-4f73-b516-bea93af1f4cb","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"In the codebase at /Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/stepml-worktrees/round4-idea-2-cycle-time-regression, find how the workload spec v2 format is validated and what fields are required. I need to understand:\n\n1. What fields does a workload spec v2 need to be valid? Look at sim/workload/spec.go for validation\n2. How does the inference_perf section get handled?\n3. Are there example workload specs in the codebase?\n\nFocus on: sim/workload/spec.go, sim/workload/inference_perf.go, examples/","agentId":"ad331cf","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a comprehensive picture. Here is a detailed report of my findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. WorkloadSpec v2 Validation -- Required Fields and Rules\n\n**File:** `/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/stepml-worktrees/round4-idea-2-cycle-time-regression/sim/workload/spec.go`\n\n### Top-Level `WorkloadSpec` Struct (lines 41-51)\n\n```go\ntype WorkloadSpec struct {\n    Version       string            `yaml:\"version\"`\n    Seed          int64             `yaml:\"seed\"`\n    Category      string            `yaml:\"category\"`\n    Clients       []ClientSpec      `yaml:\"clients\"`\n    AggregateRate float64           `yaml:\"aggregate_rate\"`\n    Horizon       int64             `yaml:\"horizon,omitempty\"`\n    NumRequests   int64             `yaml:\"num_requests,omitempty\"`\n    ServeGenData  *ServeGenDataSpec `yaml:\"servegen_data,omitempty\"`\n    InferencePerf *InferencePerfSpec `yaml:\"inference_perf,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Validation Rules (from `Validate()` at lines 167-183)\n\nThe `Validate()` method enforces these constraints at the top level:\n\n1. **`category`** -- Must be one of: `\"\"` (empty), `\"language\"`, `\"multimodal\"`, `\"reasoning\"`. Anything else produces an error.\n\n2. **`aggregate_rate`** -- Must be **strictly positive** (> 0). This is always required.\n\n3. **`clients`** -- At least one client is required, **unless** `servegen_data` is provided. The check is: `len(s.Clients) == 0 && s.ServeGenData == nil` produces an error.\n\n4. Each client in the `clients` array is validated individually via `validateClient()`.\n\n### Per-Client Validation (`validateClient()` at lines 185-217)\n\nEach `ClientSpec` is validated with these rules:\n\n| Field | Requirement |\n|---|---|\n| `slo_class` | Must be one of: `\"\"`, `\"critical\"`, `\"standard\"`, `\"sheddable\"`, `\"batch\"`, `\"background\"` |\n| `rate_fraction` | Must be **strictly positive** (> 0) |\n| `arrival.process` | Must be one of: `\"poisson\"`, `\"gamma\"`, `\"weibull\"`, `\"constant\"` |\n| `arrival.cv` (optional) | If provided, must be finite and positive. If process is `\"weibull\"`, additionally constrained to `[0.01, 10.4]` |\n| `prefix_length` | Must be non-negative (>= 0) |\n| `input_distribution` | Validated via `validateDistSpec()` |\n| `output_distribution` | Validated via `validateDistSpec()` |\n\n### Distribution Validation (`validateDistSpec()` at lines 219-229)\n\nEach `DistSpec` is validated:\n\n| Field | Requirement |\n|---|---|\n| `type` | Must be one of: `\"gaussian\"`, `\"exponential\"`, `\"pareto_lognormal\"`, `\"empirical\"`, `\"constant\"` |\n| `params` (map values) | Every value must be finite -- no `NaN` or `Inf` allowed |\n\n### Loading and Strict Parsing (`LoadWorkloadSpec()` at lines 151-164)\n\nWhen loading from YAML:\n- **Strict YAML parsing** is enabled via `decoder.KnownFields(true)` (Rule R10) -- any unrecognized/typo'd YAML key is rejected as an error.\n- After parsing, `UpgradeV1ToV2()` is automatically called, which maps deprecated v1 SLO class names (`\"realtime\"` -> `\"critical\"`, `\"interactive\"` -> `\"standard\"`) and sets `Version` to `\"2\"`.\n\n### Fields That Are NOT Explicitly Validated\n\nThese fields exist in the struct but are not checked by `Validate()`:\n- `version` -- Set automatically by `UpgradeV1ToV2()` but not range-checked.\n- `seed` -- No validation (any int64 is accepted).\n- `horizon` -- No validation (optional, omitempty).\n- `num_requests` -- No validation (0 = unlimited).\n- Client-level: `id`, `tenant_id`, `model`, `prefix_group`, `streaming`, `network`, `lifecycle`, `multimodal`, `reasoning` -- These are present in the struct but not validated by `Validate()`.\n\n### Valid Value Registries (lines 134-147)\n\nThe valid values are stored in unexported maps (per Rule R8), with a public accessor `IsValidSLOClass()`:\n\n```go\nvalidArrivalProcesses: \"poisson\", \"gamma\", \"weibull\", \"constant\"\nvalidDistTypes:        \"gaussian\", \"exponential\", \"pareto_lognormal\", \"empirical\", \"constant\"\nvalidCategories:       \"\", \"language\", \"multimodal\", \"reasoning\"\nvalidSLOClasses:       \"\", \"critical\", \"standard\", \"sheddable\", \"batch\", \"background\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. InferencePerf Section Handling\n\n**File:** `/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/stepml-worktrees/round4-idea-2-cycle-time-regression/sim/workload/inference_perf.go`\n\n### What It Is\n\nThe `inference_perf` block is an alternative, compact format for specifying workloads. Instead of manually defining many clients, you provide stage-based load patterns and shared prefix parameters, and BLIS expands them into a full `WorkloadSpec` with auto-generated clients.\n\n### InferencePerfSpec Struct (lines 14-17)\n\n```go\ntype InferencePerfSpec struct {\n    Stages       []StageSpec       `yaml:\"stages\"`\n    SharedPrefix *SharedPrefixSpec `yaml:\"shared_prefix\"`\n}\n```\n\n### StageSpec (lines 20-23)\n\n```go\ntype StageSpec struct {\n    Rate     float64 `yaml:\"rate\"`     // requests per second\n    Duration int64   `yaml:\"duration\"` // seconds\n}\n```\n\n### SharedPrefixSpec (lines 26-33)\n\n```go\ntype SharedPrefixSpec struct {\n    NumUniqueSystemPrompts  int  `yaml:\"num_unique_system_prompts\"`\n    NumUsersPerSystemPrompt int  `yaml:\"num_users_per_system_prompt\"`\n    SystemPromptLen         int  `yaml:\"system_prompt_len\"`\n    QuestionLen             int  `yaml:\"question_len\"`\n    OutputLen               int  `yaml:\"output_len\"`\n    EnableMultiTurnChat     bool `yaml:\"enable_multi_turn_chat\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Validation Rules (`validateInferencePerfSpec()` at lines 37-72)\n\n| Field | Requirement |\n|---|---|\n| `stages` | At least one stage required |\n| `stages[i].duration` | Must be positive (> 0) |\n| `stages[i].rate` | Must be finite and positive (no NaN, no Inf, > 0) |\n| `shared_prefix` | **Required** (cannot be nil) |\n| `shared_prefix.num_unique_system_prompts` | Must be positive (> 0) |\n| `shared_prefix.num_users_per_system_prompt` | Must be positive (> 0) |\n| `shared_prefix.system_prompt_len` | Must be non-negative (>= 0) |\n| `shared_prefix.question_len` | Must be non-negative (>= 0) |\n| `shared_prefix.output_len` | Must be non-negative (>= 0) |\n\n### Expansion to Full WorkloadSpec (`ExpandInferencePerfSpec()` at lines 77-157)\n\nThe expansion works as follows:\n\n1. **Validates** the spec first.\n2. Computes `numClients = NumUniqueSystemPrompts * NumUsersPerSystemPrompt`.\n3. Computes `aggregate_rate` as the **time-weighted average** across all stages: `sum(rate_i * duration_i) / sum(duration_i)`.\n4. Converts multi-stage specs into **lifecycle windows** (start/end in microseconds). Single-stage specs get no lifecycle windows (always active).\n5. Generates `N * M` clients, each with:\n   - **ID**: `prompt-{p}-user-{u}`\n   - **Tenant ID**: `prompt-{p}` (same as prefix group)\n   - **SLO class**: `\"batch\"`\n   - **Rate fraction**: `1.0 / numClients` (evenly distributed)\n   - **Arrival process**: `\"poisson\"`\n   - **Input distribution**: constant at `question_len`\n   - **Output distribution**: constant at `output_len`\n   - **Prefix group**: `prompt-{p}`\n   - **Prefix length**: `system_prompt_len`\n6. If `enable_multi_turn_chat` is true, each client also gets a `ReasoningSpec` with 5 rounds, 500ms think time, and `\"accumulate\"` context growth. The category is set to `\"reasoning\"` instead of `\"language\"`.\n\nThe output is a standard `WorkloadSpec` with `Version: \"2\"`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Example Workload Specs in the Codebase\n\nAll examples are in `/Users/dipanwitaguhathakurta/Downloads/inference-sim-package/stepml-worktrees/round4-idea-2-cycle-time-regression/examples/`.\n\n### Workload Spec Examples (what you feed via `--workload-spec`)\n\n| File | Format | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `servegen-language.yaml` | v2 native | Two clients (batch + critical), demonstrates pareto_lognormal input dist, gamma arrivals, network specs, prefix groups. Has `num_requests: 500`. |\n| `prefix-affinity-demo.yaml` | v2 native | Two clients (80/20 split), long prefix group for prefix-affinity routing demos. |\n| `multiturn-chat-demo.yaml` | v2 native | Single client with `reasoning` spec (multi-turn, 5 rounds, context accumulation). Category: `\"reasoning\"`. |\n| `inference-perf-shared-prefix.yaml` | inference_perf format (v1) | Compact format: 2 stages (8 req/s ramp-up, 20 req/s burst), 9 prompts x 5 users = 45 auto-generated clients. |\n\n### Policy Config Examples (not workload specs, but used alongside them)\n\n| File | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `epp-estimate-prefix.yaml` | llm-d EPP estimate prefix-cache config mapped to BLIS policy |\n| `epp-precise-prefix.yaml` | llm-d EPP precise prefix-cache config (2:1:1 weights) |\n| `weighted-routing.yaml` | Composable scorer pipeline demo (3:2:2 default profile) |\n| `policy-config.yaml` | General policy config example |\n\n### Concrete Example: Minimal Valid v2 Workload Spec\n\nBased on the validation rules, a minimal valid v2 spec would need:\n\n```yaml\nversion: \"2\"\nseed: 42\naggregate_rate: 10.0      # required, must be > 0\n\nclients:                   # at least one client (unless servegen_data)\n  - rate_fraction: 1.0     # required, must be > 0\n    arrival:\n      process: poisson     # required, must be valid process\n    input_distribution:\n      type: gaussian       # required, must be valid dist type\n      params:\n        mean: 128\n        std_dev: 50\n    output_distribution:\n      type: exponential    # required, must be valid dist type\n      params:\n        mean: 64\n```\n\n### Concrete Example: Minimal Valid inference_perf Spec\n\n```yaml\nversion: \"1\"\nseed: 42\naggregate_rate: 8.0\n\ninference_perf:\n  stages:\n    - rate: 8.0\n      duration: 600\n  shared_prefix:\n    num_unique_system_prompts: 3\n    num_users_per_system_prompt: 2\n    system_prompt_len: 100\n    question_len: 200\n    output_len: 100\n    enable_multi_turn_chat: false\n```\n\nNote that the `inference_perf` spec still requires `aggregate_rate > 0` and either clients or servegen_data to pass the top-level `Validate()`. However, the `ExpandInferencePerfSpec()` function produces a complete `WorkloadSpec` with auto-generated clients, so callers typically use the expanded result rather than calling `Validate()` on the original spec containing the `inference_perf` block."}],"totalDurationMs":79372,"totalTokens":3168,"totalToolUseCount":12,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":3167,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
